**Lemma 2 (Sawin, 2026).** *Lattice geometry of unit distances.*

Let `d ‚â• 1`, `R ‚â• 2`, and suppose `Œõ ‚äÇ EuclideanSpace ‚Ñù (Fin (2*d))` is a full-rank `‚Ñ§`-lattice
equipped with an additive embedding `œÄ : Œõ ‚Üí+ ‚Ñù¬≤`. Suppose `S ‚äÇ Œõ` is a finite set of "matching"
vectors satisfying `‚Äñv‚Äñ ‚â§ 1` and `‚ÄñœÄ v‚Äñ = 1` for every `v ‚àà S`, with `œÄ` injective on the
`‚Ñ§`-submodule generated by `S`. Then there exists a finite point set `U ‚äÇ ‚Ñù¬≤` such that

  `(unitDistancePairsCount U : ‚Ñù) / (U.card : ‚Ñù) ‚â• (1 - 1/R)^(2*d) * S.card`.

Proved as Lemma 2 of [arXiv:2605.20579](https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20579).
-/
@[category research solved, AMS 52]
theorem lemma_2_lattice_to_unit_distances
    (d : ‚Ñï) (hd : 1 ‚â§ d) (R : ‚Ñù) (hR : 2 ‚â§ R)
    (Œõ : Submodule ‚Ñ§ (EuclideanSpace ‚Ñù (Fin (2*d))))
    (œÄ : Œõ ‚Üí+ ‚Ñù¬≤) (hœÄ : Function.Injective œÄ)
    (S : Finset Œõ)
    (hS_norm : ‚àÄ v ‚àà S, ‚Äñ(v : EuclideanSpace ‚Ñù (Fin (2*d)))‚Äñ ‚â§ 1)
    (hS_proj : ‚àÄ v ‚àà S, ‚ÄñœÄ v‚Äñ = 1) :
    ‚àÉ U : Finset ‚Ñù¬≤, 0 < U.card ‚àß
      ((1 : ‚Ñù) - 1/R) ^ (2*d) * (S.card : ‚Ñù) * (U.card : ‚Ñù) ‚â§
        (unitDistancePairsCount U : ‚Ñù) := by
