/--
**Lemmas 11 & 12 (Sawin, 2026).** *Existence of a totally real tower with bounded root
discriminant and many split primes.*

There exists `rdBound : ‚Ñù` such that for every `N : ‚Ñï` one can find a totally real number field
`F / ‚Ñö` of degree `‚â• N` with absolute root discriminant `|disc F|^{1/[F:‚Ñö]} ‚â§ rdBound` and with
infinitely many rational primes splitting completely in `F`.

Proved as Lemmas 11‚Äì12 of [arXiv:2605.20579](https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20579), via the
Golod‚ÄìShafarevich inequality for pro-2 groups together with the Hajir‚ÄìMaire‚ÄìRamakrishna
(2003) tower construction. Both ingredients are currently absent from Mathlib, so the *formal*
verification of this statement remains a substantial sub-challenge.

Compare `Arxiv.¬´2605.20695¬ª.prop_2_3_totally_real_tower`, which refines this by requiring
that infinitely many of the split primes lie in the residue class `q ‚â° 1 (mod 4)`.
-/
@[category research solved, AMS 11]
theorem lemmas_11_12_tower :
    ‚àÉ (rdBound : ‚Ñù),
      ‚àÄ N : ‚Ñï, ‚àÉ (F : Type) (_ : Field F) (_ : CharZero F) (_ : NumberField F)
        (_ : NumberField.IsTotallyReal F),
        N ‚â§ Module.finrank ‚Ñö F ‚àß
        (|(NumberField.discr F : ‚Ñù)|) ^ ((1 : ‚Ñù) / Module.finrank ‚Ñö F) ‚â§ rdBound ‚àß
        {q : ‚Ñï | q.Prime ‚àß ‚àÉ (factors : Finset (Ideal (ùìû F))),
          factors.card = Module.finrank ‚Ñö F ‚àß
          ‚àÄ p ‚àà factors, p.IsMaximal ‚àß (q : ùìû F) ‚àà p}.Infinite := by
  sorry

/--
**Theorem 1 (Sawin, 2026).** *Explicit lower bound for the unit-distance count.*

There is an absolute constant `C > 0` such that for arbitrarily large `n` there exists a finite
set `U ‚äÇ ‚Ñù¬≤` with `U.card = n` realising at least `n^{1.014114} / C` unit-distance pairs.

Proved as Theorem 1 of [arXiv:2605.20579](https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20579). Together with
the constructive form recorded in `Erdos90.erdos_90.variants.sawin_explicit`, this is the
headline disproof of Erd≈ës Problem 90.
-/
@[category research solved, AMS 52]
theorem theorem_1_explicit_lower_bound :
    ‚àÉ C > (0 : ‚Ñù),
      {n : ‚Ñï | ‚àÉ U : Finset ‚Ñù¬≤, U.card = n ‚àß
        (n : ‚Ñù) ^ ((1014114 : ‚Ñù) / 1000000) ‚â§ C * (unitDistancePairsCount U : ‚Ñù)}.Infinite := by
  sorry

